        <svcsubproc>
            <title>General Information</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The torque values are for fasteners that have a light application of oil on the
                    threads.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the fasteners are dry, increase the torque values by ten percent (10%).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the fasteners have a heavy application of oil on the threads, decrease the torque
                    values by ten percent (10%).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If you do not know the size of the fastener that is being installed, measure the
                    fastener. Use the following procedure.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>American Standard Fasteners</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure the diameter of the threads in inches, dimension X (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f14006e8">Figure 148</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f14006e8" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g14006e8" filename="../figg14/G14006e8.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 148. Measure Diameter of Threads and Count Amount of Threads in One Inch</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Count the amount of threads in one inch (1.0 inch) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f14006e8">Figure 148</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Metric Fasteners</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure the diameter of the threads in millimeters (mm), dimension X (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f14006e9">Figure 149</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f14006e9" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g14006e9" filename="../figg14/G14006e9.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 149. Measure Diameter of Threads in Millimeters</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure the distance of ten (10) threads, point to point in millimeters (mm), dimension
                    Y. Make a note of dimension Y (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f14006e9">Figure 149</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Divide dimension Y by ten (10). The result will be the distance between two threads or
                    pitch.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
